This repository contains the INSTALL files used to build packages for yoinklinux.

To install the package using yoink-build from yoink-builder, do the following:

1) Make a dedicated directory for the build.
2) cd into the directory, and put the pkg/v-e-r.INSTALL file there.
3) Rename the downloaded INSTALL file to INSTALL.
4) Run yoink-build as root.
5) If compilation is successful, the packaged software will be under /tmp.

Do note that the INSTALL files provided in this repository are used to only build the initial tarball for a given package, any modifications are done afterwards and are not tracked here.
